<subSubSection id="FBFBD0EDE8AB9D3703DE33CBFE96A793" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="type species">
<paragraph id="ADD5A9ABAF538B1F7EEF9D674B0F134A" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DA9F43892CDC5C278C85847BCBDF80B2" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName id="67C0525807B951B0FB4C52707CCCD3B9" authorityName="Boehmova &amp; Jansta" authorityYear="2022" family="Casuarinaceae" genus="Vitreostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="kangarooislandi">
<emphasis id="5326F793FE721022B3D3A5E4F7989EDE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="7D3B04E4F727BE5D8CD9059A15A84D19" originalValue="Böhmová">Boehmova</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="AB779D15A7D37D42ED09003EEA46BB88" originalValue="Janšta">Jansta</normalizedToken>
, by present designation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CF0FF24C1A1EC59533981AB54F478A2A" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="37CDE5A6B624F0E457BF15237B0A3990" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="236AB2AF174350CF1635298932C04EDF" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Named after the transparent stigma which distinguishes the new genus from other genera of 
<taxonomicName id="0B25DB51192786092EF9CB3459B56595" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Megastigmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megastigmidae</taxonomicName>
. Masculine gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8B39217CDEA4D450BBE5B9D25E01A93C" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BC18450D889396C803A0613F84C0D6BA" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D1E7A5FBEF9EF90530554FD089AB0521" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName id="118B362C8770AE838B92600FD3F24F3D" authorityName="Boehmova &amp; Jansta" authorityYear="2022" family="Casuarinaceae" genus="Vitreostigmus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Vitreostigmus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CC5875CF653EE105A7899901F7377E7A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Vitreostigmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other genera of 
<taxonomicName id="7033B4619C8A9A6380011BA5F15B4150" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1876" class="Insecta" family="Megastigmidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Megastigmidae</taxonomicName>
by the following combination of characters: clypeus medially with one tooth (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="71EDCA0419C0C98054151FF6D2533E66" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3B</figureCitation>
); F1-F5 more than twice as long as broad; each flagellomere with two (in females) or three (in males) rows of MPS (Figs 
<figureCitation id="A2BD2C45CD62785469D155AD37A259B5" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BB07AB75594676CF17787DC059C1BC6C" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="B861EAD93340ABBD0E847D892E3242B0" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi paratypes, males A habitus, lateral view (CUPC 000163) B head, dorsal view (CUPC 000163) C fore wing, dorsal view (CUPC 000163) D mesosoma, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) E antenna (CUPC 000158) F habitus, lateral view (CUPC 000158) G head, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) H fore wing, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) I propodeum, dorsal view (CUPC 000158). Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677677" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">5E</figureCitation>
); pronotal collar delimited by transverse pronotal carina and with some additional incomplete transverse striae (Figs 
<figureCitation id="335DC29192507A0FC589DE1B0C6E7ED9" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="EFBBFC923D32BB4FD6AF8832C66E03A6" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi paratypes, males A habitus, lateral view (CUPC 000163) B head, dorsal view (CUPC 000163) C fore wing, dorsal view (CUPC 000163) D mesosoma, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) E antenna (CUPC 000158) F habitus, lateral view (CUPC 000158) G head, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) H fore wing, dorsal view (CUPC 000158) I propodeum, dorsal view (CUPC 000158). Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677677" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">5D</figureCitation>
); mesoscutellum without frenal area, broadly touching transscutal articulation with small fovea separating disc of metascutellum from transscutal articulation (Figs 
<figureCitation id="D3AA54F42A4FFB482E0A2A74BA5F0F6D" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="33CADE6A63104BB7DE9D6D822D9142B6" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi paratypes females A head and mesosoma, dorsal view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, dorsal view D habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677676" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">4B</figureCitation>
); propodeum long, about 0.50
<normalizedToken id="F8435B822D28943A9F15B8909B8B16AE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad; postspiracular furrow well developed (Figs 
<figureCitation id="A5DC7AEE1ADF4820BD275C6F63062203" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="185B4FDDF0550B28F003D38F0A489FBA" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3D</figureCitation>
); lower metepisternum with propodeal foramen oval, posteriorly narrower than anteriorly (pear-like shape); surface of lower metepisternum irregularly carinated, two additional carinae originate submedially from anterior margin of propodeal foramen, going forward in parallel and turning outwards to anterior margin of metacoxal foramen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C168FC29DD4AE8017BAE5ACBD561D072" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2G</figureCitation>
); fore wing with at least two infumations; stigma large, elongated, and transparent (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="93BFDE4970E1B3D173C68BDF3F1E3915" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3G</figureCitation>
); tip of hypopygium reaching about 0.75
<normalizedToken id="FD5FDB3CF443B2E5687441D290E92C24" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
of length of gaster, but its tip narrow, fingerlike, projecting (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4CA7E70B8CB84C1DE098082FCCF8DB90" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2I</figureCitation>
); ovipositor about 0.8
<normalizedToken id="1C4B121C43FC98B980F0E229AFD8DDE2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as metasoma (Figs 
<figureCitation id="DA0C4D8704D6D0A399830D17624B441A" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Vitreostigmus maculatus holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head and mesosoma, dorsal view C head, frontal view D clypeus, frontal view E antenna, lateral view F propodeum, dorsal view (arrow indicates postspiracular furrow) G lower metepisternum, posteroventral view H fore wing, dorsal view I hypopygium, lateral view J posterior part of metatibia and metatarsi, lateroventral. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">2A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CC38F7BE3003B8354CD2E8EF8CBD5E37" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Vitreostigmus kangarooislandi holotype, female A habitus, lateral view B head, frontal view C head, dorsal view D propodeum, dorsal view E mesosoma, dorsal view F antenna G fore wing, dorsal view. Scale bars: 200 µm." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677675" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">3A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="496123FB5C2C41494A4704C938DA9F6D" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.82582.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677674" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
